{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH87X311fyJMzi8i3giE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Tests pass.\n\n**The bug:** In `src/userService.js`, the cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it ignored `opts.includeArchived`. So when some code path called `getUsers({ team, includeArchived: true })`, the archived-inclusive result got cached under a key the picker then reused for its own `includeArchived: false` (or unset) call on the same team. The picker got back the archived list even though it never asked for it, until the 60s TTL expired — exactly matching \"refreshing after a minute clears it.\"\n\n**The fix:** the cache key now includes the `includeArchived` flag, so the two variants no longer collide:\n\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${Boolean(opts.includeArchived)}`;\n```\n\n`Boolean(...)` normalizes `undefined`/`false` to the same `false` key so the common \"not archived\" path shares one cache entry rather than fragmenting.\n\nNote: the existing test suite only covers `cache.js`, so it doesn't exercise this path — it passes but doesn't prove the fix. If you'd like, I can add a `userService` test that asserts two calls with different `includeArchived` values don't return each other's cached results."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":23221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c7698ad-1ed1-4281-81aa-ae5ca7b2193a","uuid":"4e80b291-9eae-4903-8b4e-4e6844b94925","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:49:25.264Z","request_id":"req_011CdH87VQmL9BrmmvZVHtoq"}
